description.narrative: support Generation Unlimited initiative and the Year of Youth in Kazakhstan in 2019, UNICEF, NGO and local authorities established partnership for adolescent skills-building which leveraged resources to benefit over 10,000 adolescents, including most vulnerable and living in remote rural areas. UNICEF model on Adolescent Mental Health Promotion and Suicide Prevention has been included into the new State Education Programme for 2020-2025 to further build on the decreasing rate of adolescents' suicides. Kazakhstan experience in promoting adolescent mental health and wellbeing has been shared at the global and regional levels by UNICEF, including Leading Minds for Children and Young People conference. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/01/2020
